As the treatment of Sheikh Ibrahim Zakzaky in India become difficult owing to is refusal to accept doctors other than those booked for him, the Islamic Movement of Nigeria’s leader has decided to head back to Nigeria.
He departed New Delhi in a commercial airline at 5pm Nigerian time.
In a message sent through his office, the Sheikh said he had decided to return to the country.
A top member of of Islamic Human Right Commission (IHRC) which negotiated the medical treatment in India said that the Nigerian government’s interference made the arrangement difficult.
 

			
